        "## Overview\n",
        "\n",
        "This group project was conducted in partnership with Swapfiets, the world's largest bicycle subscription service. Our team developed a marketing strategy to increase Swapfiets' customer base in Karlsruhe, Germany, with a focus on the winter months. We applied the Sinus-Milieus model for market segmentation, conducted primary survey research, and proposed guerrilla marketing campaigns targeting the Escapist milieu.\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "View the full report: [Swapfiets Report (PDF)](../../files/swapfiets-report.pdf){target=\"_blank\"}\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "## Market Segmentation: Sinus-Milieus"
      ],
      "id": "906c7717"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "milieus = ['High Achiever', 'Socio-ecological', 'Escapist', \n",
        "           'Movers & Shakers', 'New Middle Class']\n",
        "share = [27, 16, 15, 10, 8]\n",
        "colors = ['#5bcefa', '#7c73ff', '#2ecc71', '#e74c3c', '#f39c12']\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
        "wedges, texts, autotexts = ax.pie(share, labels=milieus, colors=colors,\n",
        "                                   autopct='%1.0f%%', startangle=90,\n",
        "                                   textprops={'color': 'white', 'fontsize': 11})\n",
        "ax.set_title('Sinus-Milieus Distribution in Karlsruhe', fontsize=14, color='white')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "3a2c0da3",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
