        "## Key Findings\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Escapist milieu** was selected as the primary target group due to the greatest market potential (~29,300 people) and strongest alignment with Swapfiets' service\n",
        "- **Chinese students at KIT** represented a high-potential niche with 90.91% interest rate, driven by an existing bike-sharing culture\n",
        "- **Winter tires** were the most requested addition across all milieus, with 33 total responses\n",
        "- Marketing strategy proposed poster campaigns and guerrilla marketing including mural art and a cycling parade\n",
        "\n",
        "## Reflection\n",
        "\n",
        "This was my first experience working with a company on a live business problem, through the university course. Leading a team of five through research, survey design, and strategy taught me how to combine different perspectives into one clear deliverable. Conducting street surveys in Karlsruhe gave me hands-on experience with primary data collection and its challenges. Our findings eventually led to the execution of a similar strategy by the company."
